PROGRAM
.br
.in +5
.bd
unrot
- reformats lines produced by
.bd
kwic


.in -5
.bd
USAGE           
.in +5
.br
.bd
unrot


.in -5
.bd
FUNCTION
.in +5
.br
.fi
This is a special purpose program for use with
.bd
kwic
- the key word in context index generator.
Output is assumed to be destined for printing on
an 80 character wide device.
.bd
Unrot
reads the standard input and writes the standard output.
A dollar sign ($) is assumed to be the
folding marker put in by
.bd
kwic.
A blank column running down the middle of the page will be produced.
To the right of the middle column will be keywords with following
context.  To the left will be context preceding the keyword in the 
original line.
.sp
.in -5
.bd
EXAMPLE
.br
.in +5
.nf
To create a keyword in context index:
.sp
.in +8
.bd
kwic <file >temp1
.br
.bd
sort <temp1 >temp2
.br
.bd
unrot <temp2 >index
.br
.sp
.in -8
.in -5
